1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,110
Starter Clinic Follow-up Board demo for Sparsh Hair Skin Dermatology Clinic.

2
00:00:05,060 --> 00:00:08,365
This demo is for a very simple problem.

3
00:00:08,365 --> 00:00:15,709
Clinics receive enquiries from WhatsApp, phone calls, Google, Instagram, and website forms.

4
00:00:15,709 --> 00:00:20,144
But when everything is scattered, follow-up depends on memory.

5
00:00:20,144 --> 00:00:23,461
One patient asks about hair fall timing.

6
00:00:23,461 --> 00:00:30,516
Another asks for an acne consultation after six PM. Someone else gives a missed call and waits for callback.

7
00:00:30,516 --> 00:00:36,093
If staff is busy, these warm enquiries can get delayed or completely missed.

8
00:00:36,093 --> 00:00:39,230
The requirement is not a heavy CRM.

9
00:00:39,230 --> 00:00:46,033
Sparsh first needs a practical follow-up board where every enquiry stays visible until someone closes it.

10
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:54,819
The owner should be able to see what is new, what needs appointment confirmation, what needs callback, and what has already been handled.

11
00:00:54,819 --> 00:01:00,564
So in the Starter package, AICloudStrategist builds a simple clinic enquiry board.

12
00:01:00,564 --> 00:01:03,834
Every enquiry becomes a small card.

13
00:01:03,834 --> 00:01:12,331
The board has four useful sections: New Enquiries, Appointment Requests, Staff Follow-up, and Closed or Summary.

14
00:01:12,331 --> 00:01:18,617
A WhatsApp message like, hair fall consultation timing, appears under New Enquiries.

15
00:01:18,617 --> 00:01:23,545
If the person wants a slot, staff moves it to Appointment Requests.

16
00:01:23,545 --> 00:01:28,149
If callback is needed, it goes to Staff Follow-up with a reminder.

17
00:01:28,149 --> 00:01:34,326
Once the enquiry is booked, not interested, or completed, it moves to Closed.

18
00:01:34,326 --> 00:01:37,487
The components are intentionally simple.

19
00:01:37,487 --> 00:01:39,903
A clinic enquiry board.

20
00:01:39,903 --> 00:01:43,593
WhatsApp click-to-chat or enquiry form capture.

21
00:01:43,593 --> 00:01:48,870
Basic reply templates for timing, location and appointment confirmation.

22
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:54,002
A daily owner summary showing new, pending, booked and missed follow-ups.

23
00:01:54,002 --> 00:02:01,983
And a privacy-safe setup: no diagnosis, no treatment advice, and no patient medical records in the demo.

24
00:02:01,983 --> 00:02:04,675
The benefit for the clinic is clear.

25
00:02:04,675 --> 00:02:08,954
Warm leads do not disappear inside WhatsApp chat history.

26
00:02:08,954 --> 00:02:12,055
Reception knows what needs action today.

27
00:02:12,055 --> 00:02:16,346
The owner gets visibility without checking every staff phone.

28
00:02:16,346 --> 00:02:21,875
Patients get faster replies for timings, location and appointment requests.

29
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:30,360
And the clinic can start small, then later upgrade to Growth automation or an advanced WhatsApp API workflow only if needed.

30
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:37,572
For Sparsh, the first step is only a ten to fifteen minute walkthrough of this starter board using sample data.

31
00:02:37,572 --> 00:02:43,882
After that, we understand their real enquiry process and suggest the smallest practical pilot.

